          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>8 fol. on parchment; Shelfmark: Marcel 64; Qurʾānic Text: Q 2:1-2:179; 5 lines per page; Dimensions:  325 x 228mm; Script style: kūfi D.III.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The fragments <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/626/page/1r">Arabe 351</ref> (BNF) and maybe <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/2287/page/1r">Marcel 68</ref>, <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/2288/page/1r">Marcel 69</ref> and <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/2289/page/1r">Marcel 71</ref> (NLR) belong to the same manuscript.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The catalogue entry by Valery V. Polosin (1939-2014) contains the following information:</p>
              <p>"<hi rend="bold">Marcel 64</hi></p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Two fragments</hi>: <hi rend="bold">2</hi>:1(1)–5(6); <hi rend="bold">2</hi>:170(175)–175(179).</p>
              <p>8 fol. 228×325 mm (1.43). <hi rend="bold">Support</hi>: thin transparent parchment, smooth, wrinkled in some places, of yellowish color. <hi rend="bold">Writing </hi><hi rend="bold">material</hi>: dark brown, almost black ink. </p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Collation</hi>: fragments of two quires; fol. 1 and 2, 3 and 6, 4 and 5 are bifolia, fol. 7 and 8 are singletons with stubs.</p>
              <p>I: H1F / F2H</p>
              <p>II:<hi rend="bold"> </hi><hi rend="italic">S S H3F</hi> H4F / F5H<hi rend="italic"> </hi>F6H<hi rend="italic"> </hi>F7H F8H</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Text </hi><hi rend="bold">layout</hi>: 108/110×199/200/216 mm (1.8/2.0), 5 lines. <hi rend="bold">Ruling</hi>: absent.<hi rend="bold"> </hi><hi rend="bold">Script</hi>: bold D III. <hi rend="bold">Diacritics</hi>: absent.<hi rend="bold"> Vocalization</hi>: red blue and green round dots.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Verse markers</hi>: for individual verses – teardrop-shaped medallions in the text line (type4.1.1) in gold and colors, with the inscribed word اية; for groups of five verses – medallion in the text ine (type), in gold, green and red paint, with the inscribed word خمس (fol. 3v).</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Inscriptions</hi>: numbers of surahs in Roman numerals and the verse numbers in Arabic numerals are inscribed in pencil on the upper margins of all sheets.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Defects</hi>: minor stains; parchment of the lower margins of fol 1-2 has been deformed due to moisture damage; small holes on the margins of fol. 2; ink on fol. 2v blurred; ink has partly peeled off on some pages. </p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Attached materials: </hi>old wrapping (fol. I) consisting of a narrow strip of paper inscribed with the letters “<hi rend="italic">AA</hi>”, brief description of the manuscript in French in brown ink and old accession number “<hi rend="italic">B. 41”; on the verso side the name “Monsieur Merlin</hi>” inscribed in brown ink.<hi rend="underline"/></p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Old accession numbers</hi>: А.А. (on the wrapping), B. 41 (according to Langlois’ inventory).</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Contents</hi>:</p>
              <p>Fol. 1r–2v. Surah 2, verses 1(1)–5(6). Incipit: [بسملة] الم ذلك الكتاب . Explicit: أنذرتهم أم [لم تنذرهم].</p>
              <p>Fol. 3r–8v. Surah 2, verses 170(175)–175(179). Incipit: [أصبرهم] على النار. Explicit: الألباب [لعلكم تتّقون *].</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Other fragments of the same manuscript</hi>: Marcel 68(?), Marcel 69(?), Marcel 71(?) (NLR); Arabe 351 (BNF)."</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>Olga Yastrebova has translated and sometimes corrected the notes of V. Polosin. Corrected passages are marked with ОЯ (O.Ya).</p>
            </summary>
